<br><P>

<h2>Shlomo Zilberstein</h2>

<hr noshade>
Assistant Professor <br>
<!WA12><a href="http://www.cs.umass.edu">Department of Computer Science</a><br>
<!WA13><a href="http://www.umass.edu">
University of Massachusetts</a><br>
Box 34610, Lederle Graduate Research Center <br>
Amherst, MA 01003-4610 <br>
voice: +1-413-545-4189 fax: +1-413-545-1249<br> 
<hr noshade>

<br><P> 
<br><P> 

Shlomo Zilberstein is an Assistant Professor of Computer Science at the 
<!WA14><a href="http://www.umass.edu">
University of Massachusetts at Amherst</a> where he is heading the
<!WA15><a href="http://anytime.cs.umass.edu/">
Resource-Bounded Reasoning Research Group</a>.
He received a B.A. in Computer Science summa cum laude from the
<!WA16><a HREF="http://www.cs.technion.ac.il">
Technion - Israel Institute of Technology</a>,
and a Ph.D. in Computer Science from the
<!WA17><a href="http://www.berkeley.edu">
University of California at Berkeley</a>.
Professor Zilberstein is a recipient of Israel's Security Prize (1992),
an NSF Research Initiation Award (1994) and an NSF CAREER Award (1996).
His current research interests include decision theory, design of
autonomous agents, real-time planning, resource-bounded reasoning,
and reasoning under uncertainty. <P>

<hr noshade>
